{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 12:04:44.209423", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Network troubleshooting diagnosis report\\n\\nOverview of expected behavior\\n- SDN spine–leaf L2 fabric with all hosts in 10.0.0.0/24. Inter-leaf traffic should traverse spine_1. All switches are OpenFlow-controlled by 20.0.0.100 and also join the management subnet 20.0.0.0/24.\\n\\nObserved reachability\\n- Intra-leaf connectivity is normal:\\n  - host_1_1 ↔ host_1_2: OK (0% loss, low RTT)\\n  - host_2_1 ↔ host_2_2: OK (0% loss, low RTT)\\n- Inter-leaf connectivity is broken:\\n  - host_1_1 → host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\\n  - host_2_1 → host_1_1 and host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\\n  - host_1_1 → host_2_1: test timed out; consistent with the above failures\\n\\nSwitch/controller state\\n- All OVS bridges are connected to the controller (is_connected: true) and in fail_mode: secure.\\n- Management network is up:\\n  - spine_1 eth2: 20.0.0.1/24\\n  - leaf_1 eth3: 20.0.0.2/24\\n  - leaf_2 eth3: 20.0.0.3/24\\n\\nOpenFlow dataplane inspection\\n- leaf_1 flows (table 0): only per-MAC, per-port entries between its two host-facing ports (eth0 and eth1). No entries referencing uplink eth2.\\n  - Example: in_port=2, dl_src=8a:e9:a7:0d:5d:78, dl_dst=1e:c9:d4:ae:e5:aa → output:1; and the reverse.\\n- leaf_2 flows (table 0): same pattern as leaf_1; only intra-leaf host-to-host entries. No entries referencing uplink eth2.\\n- spine_1 flows (table 0):\\n  - A single drop rule: priority=100 actions=drop with counters n_packets=38, n_bytes=2280.\\n  - This indicates all packets reaching spine_1 are being dropped.\\n\\nInterface counters corroboration\\n- leaf_1 eth2: TX 19, RX 0; leaf_2 eth2: TX 19, RX 0 (suggests leaves send towards spine but receive nothing back).\\n- spine_1 eth0 and eth1: RX 19 each, TX 0 (spine receives from leaves but forwards nothing), matching the drop rule counters.\\n\\nAssessment and anomaly detection\\n- Abnormal condition: complete loss of inter-leaf L2 connectivity while intra-leaf switching works.\\n- The management/control plane is healthy (controller connected, management IPs up).\\n- Data plane through spine_1 is failing due to an explicit, high-priority drop rule and the absence of any forwarding/bridging rules for east–west traffic.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty device: spine_1 Open vSwitch data plane.\\n- Contributing factors on leaves: lack of any uplink flows (only local host-to-host flows exist), implying the controller did not install end-to-end or broadcast/unknown flooding behavior across the spine.\\n\\nLikely root cause\\n- Incorrect OpenFlow programming by the controller on spine_1: an explicit table 0 drop rule (priority=100) with no permitting/forwarding rules for inter-leaf traffic or ARP/unknown flooding.\\n- Not a controller reachability issue (controller is connected); rather, a policy/misconfiguration resulting in spine_1 dropping all traffic and leaves missing uplink flows.\\n\\nImpact\\n- All cross-leaf traffic, including ARP for remote hosts, is dropped at the spine. Hosts report “Destination Host Unreachable” because ARP resolution for remote peers fails.\\n\\nKey evidence\\n- Pings: inter-leaf 100% loss; intra-leaf OK.\\n- OVS flow tables: leaves have only local host-to-host entries; spine_1 has a blanket drop rule with nonzero drop counters.\\n- Interface stats: leaves transmit to spine; spine receives but never transmits., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='2c7e37ce-43ab-48c6-8fbb-a53bb384c956'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
